<HEADLINE> Sen. Kennedy Admitted to Hospital  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- Sen. Edward Kennedy, D-Mass., was admitted to a hospital
Sunday morning for a viral condition after complaining of back and shoulder
pain, an aide said.
</P>
<P>
	   Kennedy, who turns 68 on Feb. 22, was comfortably ``resting in good
spirits'' at Sibley Memorial Hospital, spokesman Will Keyser said. The senator
had a cough and fever Saturday and was driven to the hospital Sunday morning.
</P>
<P>
	   He was expected to remain overnight, Keyser said.
</P>
</TEXT>
