	   Tennessee's aggressive defense posed problems for Alabama, which turned the
ball over 23 times in the game.
</P>
<P>
	   The Lady Vols' shooting cooled off considerably after the fast start.
Tennessee scored just 12 points in the final 10 minutes of the half.
</P>
<P>
	   But Alabama's offensive struggles continued, and despite Johnson's six
points in the final two minutes, the Crimson Tide trailed 34-16 at halftime.
</P>
<P>
	   Shondra Johnson led Alabama with 19 points.
