<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Women's Top 25 Fared  </HEADLINE>
   By The Associated Press
<TEXT>
<P>
	   How the top 25 teams in The Associated Press' women's college
basketball poll fared Sunday:
</P>
<P>
	   1. Connecticut (20-1) did not play. Next: vs. Miami, Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
	   2. Louisiana Tech (17-2) did not play. Next: vs. Florida
International, Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
	   3. Georgia (23-2) beat No. 20 Mississippi State 83-67. Next: vs.
South Carolina, Thursday.
</P>
<P>
	   4. Tennessee (19-3) beat Alabama 65-47. Next: at Mississippi,
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
	   5. Notre Dame (19-2) did not play. Next: vs. Pittsburgh,
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
	   6. Penn State (19-3) beat Wisconsin 57-52. Next: vs. No. 17
Purdue, Sunday.
</P>
<P>
	   7. LSU (18-3) beat No. 13 Auburn 54-52. Next: at Alabama,
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
	   8. Iowa State (17-3) did not play. Next: vs. No. 22 Oklahoma,
Tuesday.
