<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No. 6 Penn St. 57, Wisconsin 52  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    MADISON, Wis. (AP) -- Andrea Garner scored 15 points and Helen Darling added
14 to lead No. 6 Penn State to a 57-52 victory over Wisconsin on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
	   Penn State (19-3, 10-1 Big Ten) built a 31-15 halftime lead with the help of
4-of-7 shooting from 3-point range.
</P>
<P>
	   The Badgers (11-9, 5-6) battled back despite poor long-range shooting. They
made only 1 of 11 tries from beyond the 3-point line, including missing all six
3-point attempts in the second half.
</P>
<P>
	   Penn State also got 11 points and nine rebounds from Maren Walseth and 10
points from Lisa Shepherd.
</P>
<P>
	   Wisconsin was led by LaTonya Sims with 15 points and Jessie Stomski with 14.
</P>
</TEXT>
