<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-06 20:19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No.13 UCSB 104, Cal St. Fullerton 64  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    SANTA BARBARA, Calif. (AP) -- Kristi Rohr scored 25 points and grabbed 10
rebounds as No. 13 UC Santa Barbara beat Cal State-Fullerton 104-64 on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
	   Erin Buescher had 24 points and nine rebounds for the Gauchos (19-3, 7-0 Big
West Conference), who won their 15th straight game.
</P>
<P>
	   Santa Barbara never trailed, opening the game with a 9-2 run that included a
3-pointer by center Nicole Greathouse with 18:18 remaining in the first half.
</P>
<P>
	   Santa Barbara led 48-22 at halftime on the strength of 20-for-35 shooting.
The Titans (2-18, 1-7) made just nine of their 32 shots in the first half.
</P>
<P>
	   The Gauchos finished with their largest output -- and second 100-point game
-- of the season.
</P>
<P>
	   Jess Hansen and Tawnee Cooper each scored 10 points for the Gauchos, while
Greathouse added nine rebounds.
</P>
<P>
	   Megan Baskins led the Titans with 16 points. Erin Whiteside finished with 10
points and 18 rebounds.
</P>
</TEXT>
