<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-06 21:40 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pistons 109, Rockets 105  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
    AUBURN HILLS, Mich. (AP) -- Grant Hill scored 36 points in his return to the
Detroit lineup as the Pistons beat the Houston Rockets 109-105 on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
	   Hill, who missed five of the previous seven games with a bruised back,
helped the Pistons win their second straight after losing eight of nine. Jerry
Stackhouse added 23 points and Jerome Williams had 19 points and nine rebounds.
</P>
<P>
	   Kelvin Cato scored 23 points and matched a career-high with 12 rebounds for
the Rockets, who played without injured Steve Francis for the second game in a
row. Bryce Drew matched his career high with 20 points.
</P>
<P>
	   Hill looked like he hadn't missed a game, scoring 18 first-half points to
help the Pistons take a 46-41 halftime lead. Kelvin Cato kept the Rockets in the
game with 15 points and seven rebounds.
</P>
<P>
	   Hill kept it up at the start of the third, scoring eight points in the first
3:30 to help Detroit extend its lead to 60-49.
</P>
<P>
	   Houston pulled within 60-54, but the Pistons went on a 9-0 run to take a
15-point lead. Terry Mills started the surge with a 3-pointer.
</P>
<P>
	   Hill finished the quarter with a driving layup, giving him 16 points in the
quarter and Detroit a 80-67 lead.
</P>
<P>
	   Houston trailed by 16 early in the fourth, but used a 13-5 run to get within
95-87 with 3:42 left. Kenny Thomas had two inside baskets during the run.
</P>
<P>
	   Williams scored six quick points, but it still wasn't enough to put the game
away. Hill's turnover gave the Rockets the ball with a minute left, trailing by
six.
</P>
<P>
	   After a basket by Drew, Hill threw the inbound pass away and Detroit fouled
Thomas. He hit both free throws to pull the Rockets within 103-101 with 40.4
seconds left.
</P>
<P>
	   But Hill calmly hit a 12-footer from the left wing, and after Cato's short
jumper, Stackhouse made a pair of free throws.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-02-06-00 2140 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000206.0188 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-06 21:50 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Trail Blazers 100, Celtics 94  </HEADLINE>
    By JIMMY GOLEN AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
	   BOSTON (AP) -- Steve Smith scored 23 and Jermaine O'Neal scored nine of his
13 points in the fourth quarter on Sunday night as the Portland Trail Blazers
pulled away from the Boston Celtics and won 100-94.
</P>
<P>
	   O'Neal came off the bench to grab eight rebounds and score Portland's first
seven points of the fourth, getting two dunks and a three-point play as the
Blazers won for the eighth time in nine games.
</P>
<P>
	   Vitaly Potapenko scored 19 for Boston and Kenny Anderson had 11 with 10
assists.
</P>
<P>
	   Antoine Walker had 14 points and 10 rebounds for the Celtics, but made just
5-of-16 shots and 3-of-6 free throws. Paul Pierce also struggled for Boston,
going 6-for-14 from the field and 3-for-6 from the line to finish with 16
points.
</P>
<P>
	   Scottie Pippen, who scored 19, hit a 3-pointer with 2.2 seconds left in the
third quarter to give the Blazers a 71-70 lead. O'Neal opened the fourth with
two offensive rebounds and a fourth-chance dunk, then answered Tony Battie's
jumper with a dunk off an alley-oop to make it 75-72 with 10:41 left in the
game.
</P>
<P>
	   After Danny Fortson made two free throws for Boston, O'Neal's layup and free
throw gave the Blazers a 78-74 lead.
</P>
<P>
	   Portland protected its lead until Boston made a weak charge in the final
minutes.
</P>
<P>
	   Walker hit a running one-hander to make it 92-88 with 1:43 left. After
Pippen made a 3-pointer from the top of the key -- his only basket of the
quarter -- Walker made another 3 to keep the lead at four points.
</P>
<P>
	   Portland made three of four free throws down the stretch to clinch it.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-NY-02-06-00 2150 </TRAILER>
